725660f-a.title: Queens: 81st Street - 19th Avenue
725660f-a.text:
81st Street (foreground hardly shown) weat side, between
Nineteenth (right foreground, not shown) and Twenty-first
Avenues (left foreground, not shown). lIn the background bevond
the bend in the road is the Riker house, a portion of which lies
in 80th Street, which when constructed will extend north and
south beyond the swimming pool at the left. Views two and three
show an old road (tracks thereon) which extends from 81st treet
to almost 80th Street. The area in the foreground is a part of
the North Beachh Amusement Park.
May 1929
Views 1,2 and 3
Engene L. Armbruster Collection
NAY BE REPRODUCED.
